\chapter{OneDrive and SharePoint files}

We want to read and write files stored in KTH's OneDrive and SharePoint
sites, to inspect folder contents in a few different ways, and to publish
modern SharePoint pages. The main constraint is still authentication: we do
not want to require a separate Entra application registration or client id
just to move a file or update a site page.

The package already has a browser-like login stack through [[ladok3]] and
[[weblogin]], so we keep reusing that authenticated session. SharePoint's
classic REST and list-view endpoints are enough for our needs, and keeping
the implementation there lets the command-line workflow stay close to the
rest of the package.

The broader URL support, browsing ideas, and page-publishing flow adapt
ideas from prototype scripts by Alexander Baltatzis.


\section{Code overview}

This module becomes [[kthutils.onedrive]]. We keep the structure simple: a
small immutable address object, one session wrapper around the shared KTH
browser session, a set of URL and REST helpers, and a Typer subtree for the
user-facing commands.
