\section{Resolving SharePoint URLs}

We accept several different kinds of input: full browser URLs, SharePoint
copy links, shared links, server-relative paths, and a few short-hands that
are convenient for command-line use. The parsing code normalises those forms
into [[SharePointLocation]] instances so the session code can stay agnostic
about which browser URL the user pasted.

The one case where we still need external configuration is a bare
server-relative personal OneDrive path. That path does not identify its host
by itself, so we keep the existing base URL lookup for [[/personal/...]]
inputs.
<<functions>>=
def get_base_url():
  """Return the configured OneDrive base URL."""
  try:
    return os.environ["ONEDRIVE_BASE_URL"].rstrip("/")
  except KeyError:
    pass

  try:
    return typerconf.get(CONFIG_BASE_URL).rstrip("/")
  except KeyError:
    raise ValueError(
         "missing OneDrive base URL; set ONEDRIVE_BASE_URL or run "
         "kthutils config onedrive.base_url --set "
         "https://kth-my.sharepoint.com")
@

<<constants>>=
CONFIG_BASE_URL = "onedrive.base_url"
@

We expand short-hands before we inspect whether the input is already an
absolute URL. Bare names become site or personal-site roots, [[kth:]] and
[[kth-my:]] choose the host explicitly, and raw server-relative paths still
resolve against the configured personal host or the main SharePoint host.
<<functions>>=
def _resolve_sharepoint_url(url: str) -> str:
  """Return ``url`` as an absolute SharePoint URL when possible."""
  url = _expand_sharepoint_shorthand(url)
  parsed = urllib.parse.urlsplit(url)
  if parsed.scheme and parsed.netloc:
    return url

  for prefix in SERVER_RELATIVE_PATH_PREFIXES:
    if parsed.path.startswith(prefix):
      if prefix == "/personal/":
        base_url = get_base_url()
      else:
        base_url = SHAREPOINT_HOST_ROOT
      path_url = urllib.parse.urlunsplit(("",
                                          "",
                                          parsed.path,
                                          parsed.query,
                                          parsed.fragment))
      return base_url + path_url

  return url
