\section{SharePoint REST endpoints}

Once the URLs have been normalised, most SharePoint endpoints are simple
string transformations. The only wrinkle is that classic REST embeds paths
inside OData string literals, so names containing single quotes must be
escaped first.
<<functions>>=
def _escape_odata_string(value: str) -> str:
  """Return ``value`` escaped for an OData string literal."""
  return value.replace("'", "''")
@

Downloads support both path-based links and file-id links. The former use
[[GetFileByServerRelativeUrl]], while the latter use [[GetFileById]].
<<functions>>=
def _download_url(location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Return the REST endpoint for downloading ``location``."""
  if location.file_id is not None:
    return (
        f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
        f"GetFileById(guid'{location.file_id}')/$value")
  path = _escape_odata_string(location.server_relative_path)
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
      f"GetFileByServerRelativeUrl('{path}')/$value")
@

Guid-only downloads still need a separate metadata lookup so the CLI can pick
the right local file name by default.
<<functions>>=
def _file_metadata_url(location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Return the REST endpoint for retrieving file metadata."""
  if location.file_id is not None:
    return (
        f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
        f"GetFileById(guid'{location.file_id}')")
  path = _escape_odata_string(location.server_relative_path)
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
      f"GetFileByServerRelativeUrl('{path}')")
@

Uploads still target the parent folder plus the file name. That lets
SharePoint create or overwrite the file in one request.
<<functions>>=
def _upload_url(location: SharePointLocation, overwrite: bool) -> str:
  """Return the REST endpoint for uploading to ``location``."""
  folder = _escape_odata_string(location.folder_relative_path)
  name = _escape_odata_string(location.name)
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
      f"GetFolderByServerRelativeUrl('{folder}')/"
      f"Files/add(url='{name}',overwrite={str(overwrite).lower()})")
@

Folder listings still rely on [[RenderListDataAsStream]] because it works for
shared OneDrive folders where the simpler [[/Files]] and [[/Folders]] child
collections can return access errors even after authentication.
<<functions>>=
def _render_list_data_url(location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Return the list-view endpoint for listing ``location``."""
  list_url = urllib.parse.quote(
      f"'{_escape_odata_string(location.library_relative_path)}'",
      safe="")
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
      f"GetList(@listUrl)/RenderListDataAsStream?@listUrl={list_url}")
@

Detailed listings still use the classic folder endpoints when we already know
the concrete folder path. That lets the long listing and recursive tree views
show sizes, timestamps, and nested folders.
<<functions>>=
def _folder_files_url(location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Return the REST endpoint for listing files in ``location``."""
  path = _escape_odata_string(location.server_relative_path)
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
      f"GetFolderByServerRelativeUrl('{path}')/Files")
@

<<functions>>=
def _folder_folders_url(location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Return the REST endpoint for listing folders in ``location``."""
  path = _escape_odata_string(location.server_relative_path)
  return (
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/web/"
