<<constants>>=
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
AZURE_AD_DOMAIN_HINT = "ug.kth.se"
@

SharePoint needs the Azure AD federated sign-in hop, KTH's SAML relay, and a
[[UGlogin]] handler scoped to the host we are about to call. We attach them
lazily so the shared session can talk to both ordinary sites and personal
OneDrive hosts.

We only ever append handlers, never replace them. Each handler is configured
identically for a given host, so [[add_handler]] --- which deduplicates by
value equality --- keeps exactly one handler of each kind per host no matter
how many operations run on the shared session. That is what makes this method
safe to call repeatedly on the session shared with [[ladok3]]: it never
mutates or evicts another module's handlers.

Scoping [[UGlogin]] by [[base_url]] (the host root) rather than by a specific
endpoint is what lets one handler serve every file, folder, and site-page
request on that host. When SharePoint answers an unauthenticated REST call
with a 403, [[UGlogin]] reads the bootstrap URL from the response's
[[X-Forms_Based_Auth_Required]] header (weblogin~1.21), so we no longer probe
each endpoint ourselves to discover a trigger URL.
<<[[OneDriveSession]] methods>>=
def _ensure_login_handlers(self, location: SharePointLocation):
  """Attach the KTH web-login handlers needed for ``location``."""
  if self.__username is None or self.__password is None:
    logger.debug("Skipping login handlers for %s because credentials are "
                 "unavailable",
                 location.site_url)
    return

  parsed_site = urllib.parse.urlsplit(location.site_url)
  site_host_root = f"{parsed_site.scheme}://{parsed_site.netloc}"
  logger.debug("Ensuring SharePoint login handlers for %s", location.site_url)
  logger.debug("UGlogin base URL is %s", site_host_root)
  self.__session.add_handler(
      weblogin.microsoft.MicrosoftLogin(domain_hint=AZURE_AD_DOMAIN_HINT))
  self.__session.add_handler(weblogin.kth.SAMLlogin(rerun_requests=True))
  self.__session.add_handler(
      weblogin.kth.UGlogin(self.__username,
                           self.__password,
                           base_url=site_host_root,
                           rerun_requests=True))
@

Write-side SharePoint APIs require a form digest. We keep the extraction in
one helper so upload and page publishing can share the same logic.
<<[[OneDriveSession]] methods>>=
def _get_form_digest(self, location: SharePointLocation) -> str:
  """Fetch the SharePoint form digest for ``location.site_url``."""
  logger.debug("Requesting SharePoint form digest from %s", location.site_url)
  response = self.__session.request(
      "POST",
      f"{location.site_url}/_api/contextinfo",
      headers={"Accept": ODATA_VERBOSE_ACCEPT})
  logger.debug("SharePoint form digest response status %s",
               response.status_code)
  response.raise_for_status()
  payload = response.json()
  try:
    return payload["d"]["GetContextWebInformation"]["FormDigestValue"]
  except KeyError as exc:
    raise ValueError("SharePoint did not return a form digest") from exc
@

