\section{The command-line interface}

The CLI stays thin. The Python session object owns the real behaviour, while
the commands only map shell arguments to the underlying helpers.
<<option and argument definitions>>=
url_arg = typer.Argument(help="SharePoint URL or server-relative path to a "
                               "file.")
folder_url_arg = typer.Argument(help="SharePoint URL or server-relative path "
                                     "to a folder.")
site_url_arg = typer.Argument(help="SharePoint site URL, shorthand, or "
                                   "server-relative path.")
output_arg = typer.Argument(help="Local output path. Defaults to the remote "
                                 "file name.")
